  "doc_id": "13811",
  "text": "The human SEPT2-SEPT6 -SEPT7 complex can be formed from recombinant proteins all lacking their predicted coiledcoil domains, suggesting that their C termini are dispensable for complex formation [CITATION_1] . Structural analysis of crystals of the human septin complex revealed that the filaments consist of an assembly of GTP binding domains. However, the coiled-coil domains of SEPT6 ands SEPT7 do interact directly with each other [CITATION_2] , suggesting that although not required for the human septin complex, coiled-coils may further stabilize filament formation [CITATION_3] . The GTP binding domains of human septin proteins can also interact with coiled-coil structures within the multiple subunit complex [CITATION_4] . This might also occur with the Drosophila septins when they assemble into complex. However, the interaction of Orc6 with the septin complex seems strongly dependent on the coiled-coil domain of Pnut.",
